headline: Who’s the Next Apple? 3 Breakout Stocks That Point the Way
summary: Editor’s Note: Every investing era has its defining moment. In the 1980s, Apple squared off against IBM. In the 1990s, Amazon reshaped retail. And now, it’s AI transforming industries at a breakneck pace. It’s a force that’s fundamentally changing how fast companies can grow, scale, and generate profits. It is therefore producing an unusual class of stock breakouts. InvestorPlace Senior Analyst Luke Lango calls these “AI Income Events” – moments when hype flips into adoption-driven growth.Invest

headline: Is It Too Late to Consider AppLovin After 390% Rally and Record Q1 Revenue?
summary: Thinking about what to do with your AppLovin stock? You are definitely not alone, and it is an interesting time to weigh your next move. Over the past year, AppLovin shares have skyrocketed by almost 390%, which is hard to ignore even for the most patient long-term investor. Just in the last month, the stock jumped over 21%, and it is up 29% so far this year. Big moves like these naturally raise the question: is the stock still a buy, or is the easy money already made?
